# Blackbird Project Walkthrough

## Summary of Work
We have successfully built the foundation for the native Kotlin Android application "Blackbird."

### P2P Networking & Game Logic
- **Serverless Hosting Models:** Integrated `Ktor` to serve an embedded WebSocket server and CIO client for peer-to-peer data synchronization.
- **Deep Links & Connection Sharing:** Implemented custom URL models (`blackbird://join?payload="..."`) containing Base64 encoded IP and Port details to allow seamless hosting boundaries.
- **Game Engine State Machine:** Designed a purely functional [GameEngine](file:///home/max/Build/Blackbird/app/src/main/java/com/example/blackbird/game/GameEngine.kt#9-254) handling the complete game loop (Deck shuffling, Dealing, Bidding logic, Trump Selection, Trick taking, and scoring) using serializable data flows.

### AI Engine (Hardware Accelerated)
- **TensorFlow Lite Engine:** Integrated TFLite libraries using both `NnApiDelegate` (for NPU/DSP) and `GpuDelegate` for high-throughput parallel leaf evaluations during Monte Carlo Tree Searches.
- **Adaptive Fallbacks:** Designed the [AIEngine.kt](file:///home/max/Build/Blackbird/app/src/main/java/com/example/blackbird/ai/AIEngine.kt) module to intelligently map inference computations dynamically depending on the device's hardware constraints.

### User Interface 
- **Jetpack Compose Native Rendering:** Pivoted away from sluggish hybrid web interfaces to 100% native Android Kotlin Composables.
- **Realistic Card Models:** Built [CardComposable.kt](file:///home/max/Build/Blackbird/app/src/main/java/com/example/blackbird/ui/components/CardComposable.kt) adding 3D shadows, border styling, and beautiful color mapping reflecting the Blackbird suit system (Red, Green, Yellow, Black, Purple).
- **Table Dynamics:** Scaled out [GameTableScreen.kt](file:///home/max/Build/Blackbird/app/src/main/java/com/example/blackbird/ui/screens/GameTableScreen.kt) featuring a felt background mapping active trick placement and the local player's dealt hand.
- **Voice Chat Push-to-Talk:** Designed [VoiceChatButton.kt](file:///home/max/Build/Blackbird/app/src/main/java/com/example/blackbird/ui/components/VoiceChatButton.kt), utilizing pointer input tap gestures hooked into [AudioStreamManager.kt](file:///home/max/Build/Blackbird/app/src/main/java/com/example/blackbird/network/AudioStreamManager.kt) via low-latency Ktor websockets. Audio is synchronously beamed to the Host and rebroadcasted to other peers `AudioTrack` output buffers.

## Playable State
The game is currently compiling successfully via Android Gradle using `assembleDebug`. The APK can be run locally on the device or an emulator to verify connection logic and screen orientation responsiveness.
